<br>
This is in no way meant to be offensive and I hope you understand my response to your request.<br>
This is not meant to be demeaning or derogatory in anyway.<br>
<br>
But I am sorry this is really not something we are going to be doing.<br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Well on Xev we have many many guilds all right around the level of Odysseys. Some slightly stronger some slightly weaker...but all able to do basically the same stuff.<br>
<br>
There is a glut at this level and a lot of racing and positioning for mobs and raid zones. We spends days running around with nothing to kill because everything worth killing has been killed the second it pops.<br>
<br>
Bringing another guild along and teaching them the ropes in HOT so they can start to farm it for better gear so they can one day be yet another competitor for a select few mobs and zones is not really a wise idea. A few guilds have progressed beyond HOT, in fact we will soon be done with HOT ourselves, but that is not really the point.<br>
<br>
Growing a guild has certain hurdles and one is gaining experience in certain zones or getting members that have that experience already.<br>
<br>
Good luck to you and if you guild grows to where it can compete for mobs and zones that we are after we will show you the same respect we like to show others.<br>
<br>
Good luck to you and your guild. <p><p>                         
